    "Bias and fairness: Computer vision algorithms can be biased and unfair if the training data used to develop the algorithms is not diverse and representative of all groups of people.",
    "This can lead to discriminatory practices and exclusion of certain groups of people in the Metaverse. 5.",
    "Transparency and interpretability: The complexity of computer vision algorithms makes it challenging to figure out how they work and how they make decisions.",
    "This lack of transparency and interpretability can make it difficult to identify and correct errors or biases in the algorithms. 6.",
    "Environmental impact: The computational power required for computer vision algorithms can have a significant environmental impact, especially if the algorithms are run on energy-intensive hardware."
